tips.text: Wide range of yogurt! If u are looking for something healthy and a fast meal. Here it is! Nice and cozy place. Only down side is the food here is abit pricy.
Keep a stack of menus at your desk at work - makes it easy to grab lunch for pals (or send them off with an order for you!)

Food here is pretty rubbish.  The carbohydrates were overcooked (soba) or cooked horribly (rice).  Meat was dry and soaked in oil.  Vegetables were too oily.  It is definitely not "healthy". 3rd visit
Great for lunch, especially the pork rice! Expect crowd.
Great view of the Marina Bay Sands. Nice open view at the upstairs bar.
Brown rice salad with some chicken and assorted veggies is good here. Really healthy options, but nice big portions also.
This is likely one of the most overrated places in Singapore; mostly by expats. It's expensive and every piece of sushi has frozen crab meat filler.

formattedAddress: The Fullerton Bay Hotel Singapore (80 Collyer Quay)

tips.text: Their salad buffet is $29 but if u wanna add meat from the carving station (roast ribeye) u pay $36. Worth the price for food and ambience!!
Classy and romantic setting, good for a date. Food is not too bad a bit expensive for what you get. Steak was ok, truffle fries were pretty good.
Delicious Thai milk tea, and pleasant staff! Try the Extra Gold version if you prefer a stronger taste of tea.
Come on Sunday.. Not many people and enjoy the meal. Thumbs up!!
don't forget to bring your tissue packets to chope seats during lunch hours
Great environment, great food

tips.text: Good food with excellent service! must try the pork rib stew during lunch! not a common korean dish found in SG
Staff were extremely friendly and helpful ! The spaces are big in size and have all the proper appliances!
Best french bakery in Singapore. Actually, best bakery period.
Portion is gigantic! Love the granola and almond milk, banana, berries smoothie (vegan!) The fry up breakfast is good too and latte is really nice! Thumbs up guys!
Fantastic food. $$$$$. You will not get out of there for less than SG$300 for two.
The prawn & asparagus is a nightmarish mix of frighteningly stale prawns & dead asparagus.
The view from the rooftop is amazing!
Try the Burgers!! A MUST 😍

Tasty breast meat along with healthy sides

Their private dinning room is fabulous!
Have you tried their coffee and toasties? Well, you should.

Fantastic food; terrible service 😡 Served by a hovering waitress who asked "Are you done with that?" and "Can you finish that so I can clear the table?" We left within 75 minutes of being seated.

Great place for food and has a wide variety of interesting rums. :)
Amazing, one of the best restaurants I've been to in Singapore or elsewhere...
Definitively the best salad I ever eat
Good quality food well priced business lunch set menu. Angus beef onglet and chips cooked perfectly, and loved the Apple crumble dessert.
Love their kimchi soup and chicken . Lots of different types of dippings for your oven baked chicken!

My best, love their earl grey lavender & rose raspberry pistachio cakes, & their wonderful matcha green teas. A wifi'd café downstairs, & a flower shoppe upstairs. Super bouquets blooms 4 all seasons.

Pork ears and the spicy oriental bolognaise are must tries.
Nice hangout place located in d CBD area.... :)
Absolutely love their milk pudding and crepe cakes!
